{
  "stem": "1799.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 718.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I had-- I had it all together up in my brain.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A lot of people that perished-- even then and before then-- perished because they were not able to think straight and protect either their hygiene, or use common sense to, to not be caught, you know, and beaten up.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was able to do that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For some reason, I possessed a certain survivorship, not all of which is something that you have.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Some of survival happens because of luck and because of circumstances that you have no control over.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But beyond that, the instances where I had to make decisions that ended up saving my life proved that, for some reason, I had a certain mental state that, that made it possible for me to exercise judgment that benefited me.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing-- that happened almost every day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Almost every day.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I saw people next to me who would, you know, like defecate in their pants, or not conduct proper hygiene, I knew that that was one way to become ill.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was one way to lose your own self-respect.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can't really describe specifically what I did, except that I do remember that in my-- basically in my common sense that I was able to generate, I knew that this whole situation wasn't going to last forever.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I had confidence that this terrible affront to humanity would end.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it gave me enough confidence to keep generating the common sense that I felt and knew I had to muster to exercise judgment.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As best as I could.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was some water.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had to go and look for it sometimes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And depending on the camp-- as a matter of fact, in Auschwitz, which I talked about, that part was, was relatively civilized.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had toilets.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
